# Publishing content to my gemini capsule

I started this by connecting to the server using Emacs and tramp and just editing the files remotely. That's never been my favorite method, so I grabbed everything, added it to Git and created Makefile to push changes to the server.

```
LOCAL_DIR=~/Sync/pub/gemlog.baty.net/content
SERVER_HOST=server01.baty.net
SERVER_DIR=/home/jbaty/apps/gemini.baty.net
TARGET=DigitalOcean

deploy: commit push
	@echo "\033[0;32mDeploying gemlog to $(TARGET)...\033[0m"
	rsync -v -rz --checksum --delete --no-perms $(LOCAL_DIR) $(SERVER_HOST):$(SERVER_DIR)

commit:
	@echo "\033[0;32mAdding changes\033[0m"
	git add -A
	git commit -m "Build site `date`"

push:
	@echo "\033[0;32mPushing repo\033[0m"
	git push origin master

.FORCE:
```
